.TH "si476x_core_i2c_xfer" 9 "si476x_core_i2c_xfer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
si476x_core_i2c_xfer \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" si476x_core_i2c_xfer
.BI "(struct si476x_core *core "  ","
.BI "enum si476x_i2c_type type "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "core" 12
Core device structure
.IP "type" 12
Transfer type
.IP "buf" 12
Transfer buffer for/with data
.IP "count" 12
Transfer buffer size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perfrom and I2C transfer(either read or write) and keep a counter
of I/O errors. If the error counter rises above the threshold
pronounce device dead.

The function returns zero on succes or negative error code on
failure.
